        <updateDate>2021-05-21T16:36:47Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Hold Congress Accountable Act</b> </p> <p>This bill withholds or eliminates the pay of Members of Congress during a government shutdown.</p> <p>Through the day of the general election in November 2022, any salary earned by Members during a government shutdown must be held in escrow and released on the last day of the 117th Congress.</p> <p>After the November 2022 general election, a Member shall not be paid for any day during which the government is shut down. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
